 appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://quadlayers.com\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">QuadLayers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Jane\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28282:\"<p>Do you want to add an extra security layer to your online store? You have come to the right place. In this article, we will show you <strong>different methods to add CAPTCHA to WooCommerce login</strong> and configure it the right way.</p>\r\n<h2>What&#8217;s CAPTCHA?</h2>\r\n<p>CAPTCHA (Completely Automated Public Turing test to tell Computers and Humans Apart) is a modern technique used to add user verification to any website or mobile app. In other words, CAPTCHAs are used to distinguish real humans from bots to make your site more secure. The CAPTCHA creates simple challenges and displays them on the front end, and the user has to solve them to access the site. Since bots can&#8217;t solve the CAPTCHA, you can filter undesired traffic and prevent bots from entering your website.</p>\r\n<p>So if you want to keep bots away from your login, registration, and other important pages, adding CAPTCHA is a good option.</p>\r\n<p>CDN providers like Cloudflare have also included this technology and allows you to add a security layer to your website.</p>\r\n<h2>Why Add Captcha to the Login in WooCommerce?</h2>\r\n<p>If you want to protect your store from spam registrations and bots, you should add CAPTCHA to your WooCommerce login. Login pages and contact forms are some of the pages that hackers target the most. That&#8217;s why using the default <a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/customize-wordpress-login-page/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">WordPress login form</a> is not recommended.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Screenshot-2021-09-16-at-10.16.08.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-186038\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Screenshot-2021-09-16-at-10.16.08.png\" alt=\"WordPress login page\" width=\"498\" height=\"646\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Screenshot-2021-09-16-at-10.16.08.png 498w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Screenshot-2021-09-16-at-10.16.08-231x300.png 231w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>As you can see, there are no additional security layers there. By using the proper account credentials, anyone can access the account. Hackers use software that tries different combinations of username and password until they find the right combination. We&#8217;ve already seen how to <a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/customize-wordpress-login-page/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">customize the WordPress login page</a> to avoid this but you should also add another security layer.</p>\r\n<p>Adding CAPTCHA to the WooCommerce login page is an excellent way to make your site more secure and <a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/prevent-ddos-attacks-in-wordpress/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">protect their websites from hackers</a>. Hackers often use software to brute force the login page and access sites. However, if you add a CAPTCHA verification box to the log-in page, the software won&#8217;t be able to complete the operation.</p>\r\n<p>After adding CAPTCHA, your login form will look like this:</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181201\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login.png\" alt=\"jane password field\" width=\"690\" height=\"660\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login-300x288.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login-768x736.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login-600x575.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Even if the user has entered the correct login credentials, they must solve the CAPTCHA before logging in to the account dashboard. </p>\r\n<p>Now that you know why you need to add CAPTCHA to the WooCommerce login, let&#8217;s learn how to do it and prevent spam.</p>\r\n<h2>How to Add CAPTCHA to WooCommerce Login</h2>\r\n<p>There are two ways to add CAPTCHA to WooCommerce:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Using plugins</li>\r\n<li>Programmatically</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Let&#8217;s have a look at each method, so you can choose the best one for you.</p>\r\n<h3>1) Add CAPTCHA using Plugins</h3>\r\n<p>There are several plugins that you can use to add CAPTCHA to your site. In this section, we&#8217;ll focus on two tools:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>reCaptcha by BestWebSoft</li>\r\n<li>Advanced noCAPTCHA &amp; reCAPTCHA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>1.1) reCaptcha by BestWebSoft</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-captcha/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">reCaptcha by BestWebSoft</a> is one of the most popular free CAPTCHA plugins available in the market. Let&#8217;s see how to set it up.</p>\r\n<h5>1.1.1) Installation and Activation</h5>\r\n<p>First, log in to your WordPress website and go to <strong>Plugins &gt; Add New</strong>. Then, search for the reCaptcha by BestWebSoft, press <strong>Install Now</strong> and activate it.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/install-recaptcha.gif\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-181189\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/install-recaptcha.gif\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - install recaptcha plugin\" width=\"1106\" height=\"634\" /></a></p>\r\n<h5>1.1.2) Configuration</h5>\r\n<p>Once you have activated the plugin, go to the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin/create\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">Google reCAPTCHA admin console</a> and complete the registration. To register for a new website, you need to enter:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Label</li>\r\n<li>reCAPTCHA type</li>\r\n<li>Domains</li>\r\n<li>Owners</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/register-a-new-site.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181190\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/register-a-new-site.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - register new website\" width=\"840\" height=\"749\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/register-a-new-site.png 888w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/register-a-new-site-300x268.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/register-a-new-site-768x686.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/register-a-new-site-600x536.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>After filling in the required information, submit the form.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/submit-recaptcha.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181192\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/submit-recaptcha.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - submit captcha\" width=\"840\" height=\"437\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/submit-recaptcha.png 918w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/submit-recaptcha-300x156.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/submit-recaptcha-768x399.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/submit-recaptcha-600x312.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>In our case, we have selected the reCAPTCHA v2, which is the simplest reCAPTCHA type available in the list.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-type.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181193\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-type.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - recaptcha type\" width=\"839\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-type.png 852w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-type-300x118.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-type-768x302.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-type-600x236.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 839px) 100vw, 839px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>There are 3 options that you can select. We recommend selecting <em>I&#8217;m not a robot checkbox</em> which is the most common validation.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have submitted the form, the platform will display two keys on the screen: the site key and the secret key.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181194\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys-1024x664.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - keys\" width=\"838\" height=\"544\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys-1024x664.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys-300x195.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys-768x498.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys-600x389.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-keys.png 1056w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 838px) 100vw, 838px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Copy them and put them somewhere handy as you&#8217;ll use them in a minute.</p>\r\n<p>Now go back to your WordPress dashboard and go to the <strong>reCAPTCHA settings</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-181195\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings-1024x549.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - recaptcha settings\" width=\"840\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings-1024x549.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings-300x161.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings-768x412.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings-600x322.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/recaptcha-settings.png 1513w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Paste the keys and before hitting the submit button, make sure that you have selected the same version you chose before. </p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-181196\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key-1024x515.png\" alt=\"paste site key\" width=\"840\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key-1024x515.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key-300x151.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key-768x386.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key-600x302.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/paste-site-key.png 1290w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Then, scroll to the bottom of the page and you will see some WordPress default pages. Select the pages you want to add CAPTCHA to. For this demonstration, we are going to select the login page, but you can also select more pages. You can also hide CAPTCHA for certain user roles.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181200\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection-1024x447.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - protect wordpress login page\" width=\"840\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection-1024x447.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection-300x131.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection-768x335.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection-600x262.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-form-protection.png 1097w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>After that, save the settings and that&#8217;s it! </p>\r\n<h5>1.3) Testing</h5>\r\n<p>To verify that everything is working correctly, go to your login page using an incognito window and you will see a CAPTCHA box below the password field.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181201\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login.png\" alt=\"jane password field\" width=\"700\" height=\"670\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login.png 775w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login-300x288.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login-768x736.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/jane-login-600x575.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>If you can&#8217;t see a checkbox in the front end, it&#8217;s because you have entered the wrong keys or selected the wrong reCAPTCHA type. Go back to the settings and double-check the plugin options.</p>\r\n<p>This is how you can add CAPTCHA to the default WordPress login page. If you&#8217;re using the default WordPress login page as the WooCommerce login page, this is a great option. However, if you are using a dedicated page generated by WooCommerce, you need to use the premium version of this plugin.</p>\r\n<p>Currently, the free version of reCAPTCHA doesn&#8217;t come with WooCommerce integration. The <a href=\"https://bestwebsoft.com/products/wordpress/plugins/google-captcha/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">premium version</a>, however, will unlock more powerful integrations and more advanced functionalities for 21 USD per year.</p>\r\n<p>After purchasing it, you need to verify the license key and then add reCAPTCHA options to the WooCommerce login, registration, or password reset fields.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/woocommerce-login-captcha.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-181209\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/woocommerce-login-captcha.png\" alt=\"woocommerce login captcha\" width=\"814\" height=\"244\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/woocommerce-login-captcha.png 814w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/woocommerce-login-captcha-300x90.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/woocommerce-login-captcha-768x230.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/woocommerce-login-captcha-600x180.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 814px) 100vw, 814px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>If you want to add a CAPTCHA field to the WooCommerce login page without paying anything, we&#8217;ve got another plugin for you.</p>\r\n<h4>1.2) Advanced noCAPTCHA &amp; reCAPTCHA (V2 &amp; V3)</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/advanced-nocaptcha-recaptcha/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">Advanced noCAPTCHA &amp; reCAPTCHA</a> is an excellent free plugin to easily add CAPTCHA to your site. Let&#8217;s see how to configure it to protect your site.</p>\r\n<h5>1.2.1) Installation and Activation</h5>\r\n<p>As usual, the first thing you need to do is install and activate the plugin on your website. Go to <strong>Plugins &gt; Add New,</strong> look for the plugin, and install it.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/install-advanced-nocaptcha-plugin.gif\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-181210\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/install-advanced-nocaptcha-plugin.gif\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - install advanced nocaptcha plugin\" width=\"1084\" height=\"704\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>After activating the tool, you will see the plugin&#8217;s settings under the <strong>Settings</strong> section.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/advanced-nocaptcha-plugin-settings.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-181211\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/advanced-nocaptcha-plugin-settings.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - advanced nocaptcha plugin settings\" width=\"201\" height=\"418\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/advanced-nocaptcha-plugin-settings.png 201w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/advanced-nocaptcha-plugin-settings-144x300.png 144w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 201px) 100vw, 201px\" /></a></p>\r\n<h5>1.2.2) Configuration</h5>\r\n<p>The configuration of this tool is minimal. Go to the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin/create\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\">Google reCAPTCHA admin console</a> and complete the registration. Remember to select the type of CAPTCHA you want and copy the site key and secret key. </p>\r\n<p>Then, select the reCAPTCHA type and paste your site key and secret key in the corresponding fields.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181212\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings-1024x775.png\" alt=\"plugin settings\" width=\"840\" height=\"636\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings-1024x775.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings-300x227.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings-768x581.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings-600x454.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/plugin-settings.png 1086w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>After that, choose the forms you want to protect with reCAPTCHA. In this case, we will select our login and registration form. After that, save the changes.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-181214\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms-1024x488.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - available forms\" width=\"840\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms-1024x488.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms-300x143.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms-768x366.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms-600x286.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/embed-forms.png 1032w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<h5>1.2.3) Testing</h5>\r\n<p>After that, it&#8217;s time to check your WooCommerce login page. Open the login page on an incognito window and you should see a reCAPTCHA box there.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-181215\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account-1024x676.png\" alt=\"login to my account\" width=\"769\" height=\"508\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account-1024x676.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account-300x198.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account-768x507.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account-600x396.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/login-my-account.png 1127w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 769px) 100vw, 769px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>That&#8217;s it! This is how you can easily add a CAPTCHA field to your WooCommerce login page. But what if you don&#8217;t want to use any third-party tools for this? You can also do it with a bit of code.</p>\r\n<h3>2) Add CAPTCHA Programmatically</h3>\r\n<p>If you have some coding skills, you can add CAPTCHA to your WooCommerce login page using PHP snippets. In this section, we will show you how you can include a Google reCAPTCHA box in the login screen.</p>\r\n<p>As we will edit the theme&#8217;s <strong>functions.php</strong> file, before starting you should <a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/how-to-backup-a-wordpress-site/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">generate a complete backup of your site</a>. Additionally, we recommend you <a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/create-a-child-theme-in-wordpress/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">create a child theme</a> if you haven&#8217;t done so already.</p>\r\n<p>For this tutorial, instead of pasting the code directly into the <strong>functions.php</strong> file, we will use the Code Snippets plugin. It&#8217;s a site-specific tool used by thousands of bloggers and developers to make the process of editing core files easier. </p>\r\n<h4>Installation and Activation</h4>\r\n<p>First, install and activate Code Snippets on your site as shown below.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/install-code-snippets-1.gif\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-178856 size-full\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/install-code-snippets-1.gif\" alt=\"install coe snippets plugin\" width=\"1122\" height=\"642\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>After activating the plugin, you will see its settings on the left-hand side.</p>\r\n<h4>Configuration</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-185794\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets-1024x632.png\" alt=\"add captcha to woocommerce login - all snippets\" width=\"840\" height=\"518\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets-1024x632.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets-300x185.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets-768x474.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets-600x371.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/all-snippets.png 1360w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Click <strong>Add New,</strong> give the snippet a name, and paste the following code:</p>\r\n<pre>add_action(\'wp_head\',function (){echo \'&lt;script src=\"https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js\" async defer&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\';});<br />add_action(\'woocommerce_login_form\',\'add_recaptcha_to_login_form\');<br />function add_recaptcha_to_login_form() {<br />echo \'&lt;div class=\"g-recaptcha\" data-sitekey=\"YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\';<br />} { ?&gt; <br />&lt;div class=\"g-recaptcha\" data-sitekey=\"YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACA el captcha&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;?php <br />} <br />add_action( \"login_form\", \"display_login_captcha\" ); <br />function verify_login_captcha($user, $password) { <br />if (isset($_POST[\'g-recaptcha-response\'])) { <br />$recaptcha_secret = \'YOUR_SECRET_KEY\'; <br />$response = wp_remote_get(\"https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api/siteverify?secret=\". $recaptcha_secret .\"&amp;response=\". $_POST[\'g-recaptcha-response\']); <br />$response = json_decode($response[\"body\"], true); <br />if (true == $response[\"success\"]) { <br />return $user; <br />} else { <br />return new WP_Error(\"Captcha Invalid\", __(\"&lt;strong&gt;ERROR&lt;/strong&gt;: You are a bot\")); <br />} <br />} else { <br />return new WP_Error(\"Captcha Invalid\", __(\"&lt;strong&gt;ERROR&lt;/strong&gt;: You are a bot. If not then enable JavaScript\")); <br />} <br />} <br />add_filter(\"wp_authenticate_user\", \"verify_login_captcha\", 10, 2);</pre>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-185800\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet-1024x650.png\" alt=\"name snippet\" width=\"840\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet-1024x650.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet-300x190.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet-768x488.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet-600x381.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/name-snippet.png 1331w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>Make sure to paste your site key and secret key in the snippet where it says <em>YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY</em> and <em>YOUR_SECRET_KEY</em> respectively. Once you have done that, save the changes and activate the snippet.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-185801\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet-1024x594.png\" alt=\"activate snippet\" width=\"840\" height=\"487\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet-1024x594.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet-300x174.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet-768x445.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet-600x348.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/activate-snippet.png 1109w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" /></a></p>\r\n<h4>Testing</h4>\r\n<p>Now, you need to check your WooCommerce login page from an incognito window. You should see a reCAPTCHA box there.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box.png\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-185802\" src=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box-1024x721.png\" alt=\"recaptcha box\" width=\"790\" height=\"557\" srcset=\"https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box-1024x721.png 1024w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box-300x211.png 300w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box-768x541.png 768w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box-600x422.png 600w, https://quadlayers.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/im-not-a-robot-box.png 1264w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 790px) 100vw, 790px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>That&#8217;s it! This is how you can add CAPTCHA to the WooCommerce login page using a bit of code.</p>\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>All in all, keeping your login page safe is essential. By using CAPTCHA on your login page, you make your site more secure and prevent unauthorized users such as bots from accessing your dashboard.</p>\r\n<p>In this guide, we&#8217;ve seen how to add CAPTCHA to the WooCommerce login page using plugins and with a bit of code. Which one should you use? It depends. Both methods will get the job done, so it depends on your skills and needs. If you are looking for an easy solution, you can use a plugin. On the other hand, if you have programming skills and don&#8217;t like to install too many plugins, you can add the code snippet provided in this tutorial.</p>\r\n<p>If you are looking for more WooCommerce dedicated tutorials, take a look at these articles:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/change-wordpress-login-page-url/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">How to change the WordPress login page URL</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/wordpress-login-not-working/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">WordPress login not working? How to fix it</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://quadlayers.com/customize-wordpress-login-page/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">How to customize the Login Page in WordPress</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Have you found this article helpful? If you did, share this article with your friends on social media to help them protect their sites. </p>\r\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://quadlayers.com/add-captcha-to-woocommerce-login/\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">How to Add CAPTCHA to WooCommerce Login</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://quadlayers.com\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\">QuadLayers</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"https://quadlayers.com/add-captcha-to-woocommerce-login/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a: